TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = non_zero_random(-4,4,1);
BEGIN_TEXT

The Taylor 
series for \( f(x) = e^x \) at a = $a  is \( \displaystyle \sum_{n=0}^\infty c_n( x-
$a )^n. \) $BR
Find the first few coefficients. $BR
\( c_0 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_1 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_2 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_3 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_4 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

END_TEXT

$ans0 =  (2.71828182846)** ($a) ;
$ans1 =  (2.71828182846) ** ($a) ;
$ans2 =  ((2.71828182846) **($a)) / 2 ;
$ans3 =  ((2.71828182846) ** ($a)) / 6 ;
$ans4 =  ((2.71828182846) ** ($a)) / 24 ;

ANS(num_cmp($ans0));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));
ANS(num_cmp($ans4));
